      "blocks": {
        "heading_axLTnn": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "<p>Bunions</p>",
            "heading_size": "title-md",
            "heading_tag": "h2",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "text_LHGLnM": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Metatarsalgia is a term used to describe pain in the metatarsal region of the foot, commonly known as the ball-of-the-foot. This condition affects the bones and joints at the ball-of-the-foot, often located under the 2nd, 3rd, and 4th metatarsal heads, or more isolated at the first metatarsal head near the big toe.<br/><br/>Improperly fitting footwear, especially women’s dress shoes and other restrictive shoes, commonly causes ball-of-foot pain. Additional causes of excessive pressure in the ball-of-foot area include high heels, high-impact activities without proper footwear or orthotics, and thinning of the fat pad in the foot with age.<br/><br/></p>",
            "text_font": "body",
            "text_size": "subtext-md",
            "text_max_size": 32,
            "text_line_height": 1.6,
            "text_letter_spacing": 0,
